            94-Room Hampton Inn & Suite Tampa-Wesley Chapel Sold by Marcus & Millichap
            






94-Room Hampton Inn & Suite Tampa-Wesley Chapel Sold by Marcus & Millichap
July 20, 2016




Share

Facebook
Twitter
Email
LinkedIn
Favorites






WESLEY CHAPEL, Fla., July 20, 2016 – Marcus & Millichap (NYSE: MMI), a leading commercial real estate investment services firm with offices throughout the United States and Canada, announced the sale of a 94-room Hampton Inn & Suites in Wesley Chapel, Florida. The terms of the sale were not released.
“Hampton Inn & Suites is a highly sought after brand, and the location at Wesley Chapel true to form generated numerous offers when the property was being marketed,” says Jonathan Ruprai, senior director of Marcus & Millichap’s National Hospitality Group in Tampa. “Attracted by the hotel’s strong performance, location and demographics, the new owner is positioned to benefit from the tremendous growth transforming Wesley Chapel.”
Ruprai, along with Dennis Hopper, a senior associate also in Tampa, represented the seller and secured the buyer, a subsidiary of Nimbus Investment Fund, LP, an independent affiliate of Emerald Hospitality Associates, Inc., based in Westlake, OH, which will manage the property.
The Hampton Inn & Suites is located in the Wesley Chapel suburb of Tampa at 2740 Cypress Ridge Blvd., and sits directly off of Interstate 75, providing the hotel with high visibility.
The Hampton Inn & Suites Tampa -Wesley Chapel has won several awards including Hilton’s companywide Circle of Excellence Award and Lighthouse Award for high rankings in accommodations, service and quality, and TripAdvisor’s Hall of Fame award for winning five consecutive TripAdvisor Certificate of Excellence Awards. 





#     #     #
About Marcus & Millichap (NYSE: MMI)
With over 1,700 investment sales and financing professionals located throughout the United States and Canada, Marcus & Millichap is a leading specialist in commercial real estate investment sales, financing, research and advisory services. Founded in 1971, the firm closed nearly 9,000 transactions in 2016 with a value of approximately $42.3 billion. The company has perfected a powerful system for marketing properties that combines investment specialization, local market expertise, the industry’s most comprehensive research, state-of-the-art technology, and relationships with the largest pool of qualified investors.  To learn more, please visit: www.MarcusMillichap.com






Related Reports

Florida Hospitality Investment Forecast
Scattered sunshine in the near-term outlook. Statewide supply growth will contribute to a decline in annual occupancy in Florida and a further moderation in the increases in ADR and RevPAR.





